**Difference between a Library and Framework?
Framework and library both are block of code written by someone else that help solve common problems in a particular programming language. 
Library is a collection of functions developers call whenever needed according to the flow/requirement. Developer has control over the code. 
Your code -> (needs some functionality) -> calls -> library
Framework is a structure to which the developer has to provide the contents of the operation. So basically 
Difference
When using a library, the control remains with the developer who tells the application when to call library functions. 
When using a framework, the control is reversed, which means that the framework tells the developer where code needs to be provided and calls it as it requires.

